						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the house of Patel Saṅkayya seṭṭi.</p>						

						<p>Bukka I, 1370 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record seems to register a gift of land to a deity at Achalāḍi when <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Gōparsa-voḍeya</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya.</hi> The details are all lost.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1293, Sādhāraṇa, dvitīya Vaiśākha śu. 1, Vaḍḍavāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1370 A.D., April 27.</hi> The weekday was Saturday.</p>						

						</summary>
